a.title: A record of food or fluid that is being consumed by a patient. A NutritionIntake may indicate that the patient may be consuming the food or fluid now or has consumed the food or fluid in the past. The source of this information can be the patient, significant other (such as a family member or spouse), or a clinician. A common scenario where this information is captured is during the history taking process during a patient visit or stay or through an app that tracks food or fluids consumed. The consumption information may come from sources such as the patient's memory, from a nutrition label, or from a clinician documenting observed intake.

a.title: Legend for this format

title.value: Cross-version Extension `R5.NutritionIntake` for use in FHIR R4

description.value: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `NutritionIntake` for use in FHIR R4.

purpose.value:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the element `NutritionIntake` as defined in FHIR R5 in FHIR R4.
The source element is defined as: `NutritionIntake` 0..* `NutritionIntake`
Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as: * R5 `NutritionIntake` 0..* `NutritionIntake`
Following are the generation technical comments: Element `NutritionIntake` is not mapped to FHIR R4, since FHIR R5 `NutritionIntake` is not mapped.

short.value: Record of food or fluid being taken by a patient

definition.value: A record of food or fluid that is being consumed by a patient. A NutritionIntake may indicate that the patient may be consuming the food or fluid now or has consumed the food or fluid in the past. The source of this information can be the patient, significant other (such as a family member or spouse), or a clinician. A common scenario where this information is captured is during the history taking process during a patient visit or stay or through an app that tracks food or fluids consumed. The consumption information may come from sources such as the patient's memory, from a nutrition label, or from a clinician documenting observed intake.

short.value: Record of food or fluid being taken by a patient

definition.value: A record of food or fluid that is being consumed by a patient. A NutritionIntake may indicate that the patient may be consuming the food or fluid now or has consumed the food or fluid in the past. The source of this information can be the patient, significant other (such as a family member or spouse), or a clinician. A common scenario where this information is captured is during the history taking process during a patient visit or stay or through an app that tracks food or fluids consumed. The consumption information may come from sources such as the patient's memory, from a nutrition label, or from a clinician documenting observed intake.
